      "id": "text_0",
      "type": "text",
      "description": "Matrix multiplication involves multiplying two matrices to produce a third.",
      "x": 80,
      "y": 450
    },
    {
      "id": "text_1",
      "type": "text",
      "description": "The number of columns in the first matrix must equal the number of rows in the second for them to be multiplied.",
      "x": 80,
      "y": 480
    },
    {
      "id": "text_2",
      "type": "text",
      "description": "To multiply, each element in a row is multiplied by corresponding elements and then those products are summed up to form an entry in the resulting product matrix.",
      "x": 80,
      "y": 510
    },
    {
      "id": "text_3",
      "type": "text",
      "description": "Matrix multiplication isn't commutative; changing the order changes the result.",
      "x": 80,
      "y": 540
    }
